comments.body:
Specifically Skopeo is not doing anything to affect the overlay graph driver; but Podman does do quite a bit more to set up the environment than Skopeo does.

Looking at the unpacking code, I’m not sure that `ignore_chown_errors` is _consistently_ applied (e.g. https://github.com/containers/container-libs/blob/1a88a3dabe07412a738101b1c5e3a797e8de0f6c/storage/pkg/archive/archive.go#L1140 ), but that would apply to Podman equivalently — so I’m more inclined to think the option enforcement, if any is at most a _part_ of the behavior difference.

@giuseppe does this ring a bell?
